    stable 1.0
  category security/encryption
 attribute console new
    source http://www.packetstormsecurity.nl/crypt/aes/aescrypt2-$VERSION.tgz
  homepage http://www.packetstormsecurity.nl/crypt/aes/
      desc 'aescrypt2 is a command line file encryption program.
aescrypt2 features strong 256-bit AES encryption, an integrity
check based on HMAC-SHA256, a stronger password hashing algorithm
that prevents fast dictionnary attacks, and largefile support on
Linux, Solaris, *BSD, and Windows.
Please note that version 1.0 is not compatible with aescrypt2-rc1.'


build(){
sed -i "s:-O:$CFLAGS:" Makefile
make clean
make &&
prepare_install &&
install -o root -g root -vm 755 aescrypt2 /usr/bin
}
